Bunuel's project was\nclear, a demystification
of poverty, camera\nwork that went
against the usual\ntechniques of social films.
The film mocks its\naudience, savagely
denying any space for\nmiddle class sentiments
as it narrates the brutalized\nexperiences of Mexico's
urban delinquents.
The use of these postcard and\naerial views in the opening
