you need somebody else\nto explain it to you.
And that person generally\nin the early years
is from the outside.
They're not from the inside,\nas we just saw in those films.
There's also an idea\nin all of these,
as I said before, that\nthis is a place apart.
It is strange.
It's picturesque.
It's fantastical.
It's grotesque.
But it is another world.
It is not the same world\nthat the presumed observers
are observing from, right?
There is this kind of\nseparation between these spaces.
There is also a notion that the\nrest of the city might exist,
but there's an invisible\nfrontier between the spaces.
It's the aerial\nphotographs that we just
saw but written into\nthese texts much
earlier than aerial photography\nwas actually existing.
And one very important\nexception to this
is the film Rio 40 Graus, Rio\n110 Degrees, which actually
