the experience of being a\nvictim of whatever problem
it is that has been identified\nby these mediators, right?
And that, of course, is very\nimportant in policy terms
because it indicates that\nthe table, the people who
should be at this conference,\nthe people who should be
at the places where\ndecisions are made,
are the ones who are observing,\nwho are being explained
to by these mediators.
They're not the people\nwho are being observed.
And I think that that's\na very important function
that a lot of\ncultural media have.
And I would even say that\na film like City of God
continues with that\nfunction, even though we're
