And then finally, I'm just\ngoing to end with one last more
provocative point, which is\nthat in emphasizing the notion
of these communities as\nbeing closed to the outside,
as being self-contained,\nas being the expression
in and of themselves\nof a problem--
that is, they are\nproblematic spaces.
Maybe they're problematic spaces\nbecause they're victimized.
Maybe they're problematic spaces\nbecause they're oppressed.
Maybe they're problematic\nspaces because the people who
live in them are somehow\nmisformed, somehow
full of anomie, or full of\nviolence, or full of rage.
Whatever the reason,\nthese are portrayed
